ent gout flare in the right great toe was successfully managed with colchicine and allopurinol. \n- Discharge Disposition: Home in stable condition with pain controlled by Oxycodone and Acetaminophen. \n- Follow-up: General surgery clinic in 1\u20132 weeks. Instructions include a regular diet, activity restrictions (no lifting >10 lbs for 6 weeks), and wound care.",
